file_path = "./Functions"
file.sources = list.files(path = file_path, pattern = "*.R$", full.names = TRUE)
sapply(file.sources, source)

# Generate synthetic data
SEED = 0 #random seed for reproducibility
N_subj = 40 #number of subjects
N_trial = 5 #number of observations
N_clus = 4 #number of clusters
N_component = 2 #number of stimuli
t_vec = seq(0, 2.5, by=0.01) #time grid on which intensity components are estimated
key_times_vec = c(0, 0.8, 2.5) #a vector where the first N_component elements are the smallest observation-specific time shifts of the N_component stimuli, and the (N_component+1)-th element is the observation end time
N_spks_total = 150 #a parameter that controls the expected number of events per subject in each observation
timeshift_subj_max_vec = c(1/16, 1/16) #a vector of the largest subject-specific time shifts in response to the N_component stimuli
timeshift_trial_max = 0.3 #range between the smallest and the largest trial-specific time shifts for any stimulus
clus_sep = 0.5 #a parameter that controls the distinctiveness of clusters

data_generated = generate_data(SEED = SEED,
                               N_subj = N_subj,
                               N_trial = N_trial,
                               N_clus = N_clus, 
                               t_vec = t_vec,
                               key_times_vec = key_times_vec,
                               N_spks_total = N_spks_total,
                               timeshift_subj_max_vec = timeshift_subj_max_vec,
                               timeshift_trial_max = timeshift_trial_max,
                               clus_sep = clus_sep)
spks_time_mlist = data_generated$spks_time_mlist
v_trialwise_vec_list = data_generated$v_trialwise_vec_list

# Visualize synthetic data
N_subj_max_display = 5

options(repr.plot.width = 7, repr.plot.height = 6, repr.plot.res=130)
plot(0,0, col = 'white', 
     cex.lab = 1.5, cex.main = 1.5,
     xlab = 'Time (sec)', ylab = '', 
     main = 'Synthetic recurrent event data (Subject 1 ~ 5)',
     yaxt='n',
     xlim = c(min(-0.25, t_vec), max(t_vec)), ylim = c(1.2, N_subj_max_display*N_trial) )
title(ylab = 'Recurrent events', cex.lab = 1.5,  line = 1) 
count = 0
for (id_subj in N_subj_max_display:1){
    for (id_trial in N_trial:1){
        count = count + 1
        spks_vec = unlist(spks_time_mlist[id_subj, id_trial])            
        points(x = spks_vec , y = 0 * spks_vec + count, pch = 16, cex = 1.3, 
               col = rgb(0,0,0,0.073))

        points(x = key_times_vec[1]+v_trialwise_vec_list[[1]][id_trial] , y = count, pch = 16, cex = 1.8, col = rgb(242, 141, 85, maxColorValue = 256))  
        points(x = key_times_vec[2]+v_trialwise_vec_list[[2]][id_trial] , y = count, pch = 16, cex = 1.8, col = rgb(76, 122, 216, maxColorValue = 256))        
    }
    text(x = -0.29, y = count - N_trial/2+0.5, 
         labels = paste('Subj',id_subj,'\nObs 1~5'), 
         cex=1.2, pos = 1, offset = 0, srt = 90, col = 
        'orange')
    abline(h = count+0.5, col = 'blue', lwd = 0.3)
}

# Set tuning parameters
N_clus_est = 4 #number of desired clusters
gamma = 0.01 #a tuning parameter that controls the relative importance of L2 compared to L1 in the optimization with respect to cluster memberships
freq_trun = 10 #frequency truncation parameter for numerical feasibility of intensity estimation
conv_thres = 5e-3 #convergence threshold

# Initialize memberships and time shifts
res = get_init(spks_time_mlist = spks_time_mlist, 
               N_clus = N_clus_est,
               N_component = N_component,
               t_vec = t_vec, 
               key_times_vec = key_times_vec,
               v_trialwise_vec_list = v_trialwise_vec_list,
               freq_trun = freq_trun,
               rmv_conn_prob = TRUE)
clusters_list_init = res$clusters_list
v_mat_list_init = res$v_mat_list

# Apply ASIMM  
res = apply_asimm(spks_time_mlist = spks_time_mlist,
                   v_trialwise_vec_list = v_trialwise_vec_list,
                   clusters_list_init = clusters_list_init,
                   v_mat_list_init = v_mat_list_init,
                   N_component = N_component, 
                   freq_trun = freq_trun,
                   gamma = gamma,
                   t_vec = t_vec, 
                   key_times_vec = key_times_vec,
                   conv_thres = conv_thres )

# Extract ground truth
center_density_array_true = data_generated$center_density_array_true
center_intensity_array_true = data_generated$center_intensity_array_true
mem_true_vec = data_generated$mem_true_vec
clus_true_list = data_generated$clus_true_list
v_true_mat_list = data_generated$v_mat_list
v_subjwise_vec_list_true = lapply(1:N_component, function(id_component)v_true_mat_list[[id_component]][,1]-
                                  data_generated$v_trialwise_vec_list[[id_component]][1])

# Find cluster label permutation
permn = find_permn_clus_label(clusters_list_true = clus_true_list, 
                              clusters_list_est = res$clusters_list)

# Retrieve estimation results
clusters_list_est = res$clusters_list[permn]
mem_est_permn_vec = clus2mem(clusters = clusters_list_est)
v_subjwise_vec_list_est = res$v_subjwise_vec_list
center_intensity_array_est = res$center_intensity_array[permn, , ]
center_intensity_baseline_vec_est = res$center_intensity_baseline_vec[permn]
center_density_array_est = res$center_density_array[permn, , ]

# Visualize clustering results 
print("Contingency table of estimated memberships and true memberships:")
table(membership_est = mem_est_permn_vec, membership_true = mem_true_vec)

# Calculate MISE for intensity components
dist_mse_mat = matrix(nrow=N_clus, ncol=N_component)
t_unit = t_vec[2]-t_vec[1]
for (id_clus in 1:N_clus) {
    for (id_component in 1:N_component) {
      f_target = center_density_array_true[id_clus,id_component,]
      density_est = center_density_array_est[id_clus,id_component,]
      res_ccf = ccf(y = density_est, x = f_target, plot = FALSE, lag.max = length(t_vec)%/%2)
      n0_init = res_ccf$lag[which.max(res_ccf$acf)]
      if (length(n0_init) == 0) {
        n0_init = 0
      }
      f_target_array = array(data = f_target, dim = c(1,1,length(f_target)))
      f_origin_mat = matrix(density_est, nrow = 1)
      n0 = align_multi_components(f_target_array = f_target_array,
                                  f_origin_mat = f_origin_mat,
                                  n0_init_mat = as.matrix(n0_init),
                                  v_trialwise_vec_list = list(c(0)),
                                  N_spks_mat = as.matrix(c(1)),
                                  t_unit = t_unit, 
                                  n0_min_vec = -length(f_target) %/% 2,
                                  n0_max_vec = length(f_target) %/% 2 )$n0_mat
      n0 = round(n0)
      if (n0 > 0) {
        density_est_shift = c(rep(head(density_est,1), n0), head(density_est, length(density_est) - n0) )
      } else if (n0 < 0) {
        density_est_shift = c(tail(density_est, length(density_est) - abs(n0)), rep(tail(density_est,1), abs(n0)) )
      } else if (n0 == 0) {
        density_est_shift = density_est
      }
      dist_mse_mat[id_clus,id_component] = sum( (density_est_shift - 
                                                   center_density_array_true[id_clus,id_component,])^2 * 
                                                  t_unit )
    }
}
F_mean_sq_err_vec = rowMeans(dist_mse_mat)
as.matrix(paste0("MISE for Cluster ", 1:N_clus, ": ",round(F_mean_sq_err_vec,3)))

                       key_times_vec = key_times_vec,
